 The drama between Nigerian superstars Burna Boy, CDQ and popular footballer, Obafemi Martins, has escalated to another level following the emergence of a video and audio recording from the night of the ugly exchange. In the clip which was exclusively obtained by Pulse Nigeria, CDQ was seen drenched in blood on his head and some parts of his outfit. A voice allegedly belonging to the rapper was heard recounting what had happened and how he sustained the injuries. CDQ claimed he was stabbed and another individual identified as Uti also sustained stab injuries. The rapper said it was so bad that he had to be taken to the hospital and given two pints of blood. The rapper also claimed that after he returned from the hospital, Burna requested for him to come to the club and make a video to let people know that the issue had been resolved. See video below